cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a new training framework for graph neural networks (GNNs) to address the problems of neighbors explosion, node dependence, and oversmoothing when facing large-size graphs and using a deeper structure. The proposed framework is evaluated on different sizes of graphs and various GNNs (GCN & GAT). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
